{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":7956,"name":"","username":"sabotage3d","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/sabotage3d/{size}/87_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-23T13:00:35.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi,\u003cbr\u003e\nI I couldn’t find in the documentation what are the supported texture compressions for Mobile. In older post it was mentioned that Urho3D is using stb_image but its a bit vague in terms of supported compressions. Where should we start if we want to add additional compressions like ASTC ? There is a also an open-source encoder and decoder for ASTC : \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/ARM-software/astc-encoder\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003egithub.com/ARM-software/astc-encoder\u003c/a\u003e . In general I don’t have a lot of experience with textures for mobile. If anyone can recommend me what would be the best compression to use would be great.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:22.948Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":62,"reads":5,"readers_count":4,"score":311.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1385,"topic_slug":"texture-compressions-for-mobile","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/ARM-software/astc-encoder","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - ARM-software/astc-encoder","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":151,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7957,"name":"Lasse Öörni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-23T14:11:56.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eMobile compressed texture loading bypasses stb_image and handles the formats directly. From the documentation:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e“ETC1 (Android) and PVRTC (iOS) compressed textures are supported through the .ktx and .pvr file formats.”\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe tools you may find that are able to generate these files may be sucky, so your mileage may vary.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you want to support additional formats, just start hacking the Image.h / Image.cpp files.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:23.008Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":6,"readers_count":5,"score":1.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1385,"topic_slug":"texture-compressions-for-mobile","display_username":"Lasse Öörni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7965,"name":"","username":"sabotage3d","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/sabotage3d/{size}/87_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-23T20:04:30.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThank you very much cadaver. Would you recommend ASTC as the best from both worlds ?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:23.580Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":5,"readers_count":4,"score":1.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1385,"topic_slug":"texture-compressions-for-mobile","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":151,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7968,"name":"Lasse Öörni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-24T07:42:52.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIt’s probably quite well covered by recent Android devices. I couldn’t get a clear answer of the iOS devices that support it, but not all do.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:23.773Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":6,"readers_count":5,"score":6.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1385,"topic_slug":"texture-compressions-for-mobile","display_username":"Lasse Öörni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7970,"name":"Justin Miller","username":"jmiller","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jmiller/{size}/2367_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-24T10:04:45.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eJust to throw in some references…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePNG/PVR comparison (slightly older)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/501956/pvr-textures-versus-png-in-opengl-es\"\u003estackoverflow.com/questions/5019 … -opengl-es\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNot a recommendation for PNG in your scenario but FYI: they can be compressed significantly more than imaging apps like GIMP do (maybe 10%, depends) using a utility like PNGOUT. It’s available for Linux/Win/Mac - \u003ca href=\"http://advsys.net/ken/utils.htm\"\u003eadvsys.net/ken/utils.htm\u003c/a\u003e - and as a plugin for \u003ca href=\"http://www.irfanview.com/\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003eIrfanView\u003c/a\u003e (MSWin). Of course as important, you’d want to select optimal bit depths.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:23.896Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":6,"readers_count":5,"score":6.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1385,"topic_slug":"texture-compressions-for-mobile","display_username":"Justin Miller","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/501956/pvr-textures-versus-png-in-opengl-es","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"iphone - PVR textures versus PNG in OpenGL ES - Stack Overflow","clicks":6},{"url":"http://advsys.net/ken/utils.htm","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Ken Silverman's Utility Page","clicks":2},{"url":"http://www.irfanview.com/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"IrfanView - Official Homepage - one of the most popular viewers worldwide","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":21,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7972,"name":"","username":"rasteron","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rasteron/{size}/55_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-24T10:33:41.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e[quote=“carnalis”]\u003cbr\u003e\nNot a recommendation for PNG in your scenario but FYI: they can be compressed significantly more than imaging apps like GIMP do (maybe 10%, depends) using a utility like PNGOUT. It’s available for Linux/Win/Mac - \u003ca href=\"http://advsys.net/ken/utils.htm\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eadvsys.net/ken/utils.htm\u003c/a\u003e - and as a plugin for \u003ca href=\"http://www.irfanview.com/\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eIrfanView\u003c/a\u003e (MSWin). Of course as important, you’d want to select optimal bit depths.[/quote]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI use PNGGauntlet (Windows) for PNG compression. It combines PNGOUT, OptiPNG, and DeflOpt to create the smallest PNGs…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://pnggauntlet.com/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003epnggauntlet.com/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:24.046Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":6,"readers_count":5,"score":6.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1385,"topic_slug":"texture-compressions-for-mobile","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://advsys.net/ken/utils.htm","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Ken Silverman's Utility Page","clicks":1},{"url":"http://pnggauntlet.com/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"PNGGauntlet - PNG Compression Software | BenHollis.net","clicks":0},{"url":"http://www.irfanview.com/","inter